definitions.definition: A woven basket , especially a wicker basket and especially as follows:

subdefinitions.definition: An osier basket that anglers use to hold fish .

Such a basket slung as a backpack for cargo , especially in times and places with limited or nonexistent wheeled transport, as for example among peasants in mountainous regions. ( chiefly historical ) Such a basket slung on a pack animal; a pannier .

definitions.definition: A bar or set of bars with skewers for holding paying-off bobbins , as in the roving machine, throstle , and mule .
